ciscoWANSonetMIB.description: The MIB module to describe SONET/SDH interfaces objects. This is an extension to the standard SONET MIB(RFC 2558).

cwsSectionAlarmTable.name: cwsSectionAlarmTable
cwsSectionAlarmTable.description: The SONET/SDH Section Alarm table. This table contains objects for setting alarm thresholds and reading alarm severity.

cwsSectionAlarmEntry.name: cwsSectionAlarmEntry
cwsSectionAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the alarm table. The entries exist for active sonet lines, with default threshold values. Thresholds may be configured for errored seconds(ES), severely errored seconds(SES), severely errored framing seconds(SEFS) and coding violations(CV) for section layer sonet lines. Once these thresholds are exceeded, minor or major alarm is raised. Please refer RFC1595 for descriptions of ES,SES,SEFS,CV

cwsSectionStatisticalAlarmSeverity.name: cwsSectionStatisticalAlarmSeverity
cwsSectionStatisticalAlarmSeverity.description: By setting this object to major or minor, a minor or major severity alarm is raised when any statistical threshold is exceeded. By default TCA crossing does not raise any alarm.

cwsSectionCurrentESsThreshold.name: cwsSectionCurrentESsThreshold
cwsSectionCurrentESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES), for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionTotalESsThreshold.name: cwsSectionTotalESsThreshold
cwsSectionTotalESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES), for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionCurrentSESsThreshold.name: cwsSectionCurrentSESsThreshold
cwsSectionCurrentSESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored seconds(SES) for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionTotalSESsThreshold.name: cwsSectionTotalSESsThreshold
cwsSectionTotalSESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored seconds(SES) for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionCurrentSEFSsThreshold.name: cwsSectionCurrentSEFSsThreshold
cwsSectionCurrentSEFSsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored framing seconds(SEFS), above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionTotalSEFSsThreshold.name: cwsSectionTotalSEFSsThreshold
cwsSectionTotalSEFSsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored framing seconds(SEFS) for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionCurrentCVsThreshold.name: cwsSectionCurrentCVsThreshold
cwsSectionCurrentCVsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for coding violations(CV), above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionTotalCVsThreshold.name: cwsSectionTotalCVsThreshold
cwsSectionTotalCVsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for coding violations(CV) for 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated.

cwsSectionStatAlarmStatus.name: cwsSectionStatAlarmStatus
cwsSectionStatAlarmStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the interface. When an alarm is raised, this would indicate which threshold was exceeded. This object is updated every 15-minutes. Once the current 15-min window has passed, and there are no errors in the current 15-min window, the object is cleared from the lower level sonet task. The cwsSectionStatAlarmStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. If none of the bits are set, it indicates no defect. The various bit positions are: 1 sonetSectionTotalESs 2 sonetSectionTotalSESs 3 sonetSectionTotalSEFSs 4 sonetSectionTotalCVs 5 sonetSectionCurrentESs 6 sonetSectionCurrentSESs 7 sonetSectionCurrentSEFSs 8 sonetSectionCurrentCVs

cwsSectionCurrent24HrTable.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrTable
cwsSectionCurrent24HrTable.description: Contains sonet section related current 24 hour counters. A 24 hour interval starts at twelve midnight with reference to node time. In case of a manual change in node time all the counters in cwsSectionCurrent24HrTable table get reset to 0.

cwsSectionCurrent24HrEntry.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrEntry
cwsSectionCurrent24HrEntry.description: An entry in the current 24 hour table. The entries exist for active sonet lines.

cwsSectionCurrent24HrESs.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrESs

cwsSectionCurrent24HrSESs.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrSESs
cwsSectionCurrent24HrSESs.description: Number of SESs encountered in current 24 hour interval.

cwsSectionCurrent24HrSEFSs.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrSEFSs
cwsSectionCurrent24HrSEFSs.description: Number of SEFSs encountered in current 24 hour interval.

cwsSectionCurrent24HrCVs.name: cwsSectionCurrent24HrCVs
cwsSectionCurrent24HrCVs.description: Number of CVs encountered in current 24 hour interval.

cwsLineAlarmTable.name: cwsLineAlarmTable
cwsLineAlarmTable.description: The SONET/SDH Line Alarm table. This table contains objects which are thresholds that the user can set. Once the threshold is exceeded, an alarm is flagged.Changing any threshold will affect both the Near End and Far End(remote end of the line) threshold.

cwsLineAlarmEntry.name: cwsLineAlarmEntry
cwsLineAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Line Alarm table. The entries may be created for an ifType value of sonet(39). Thresholds maybe specified for errored seconds(ES), severely errored seconds(SES), severely errored framing seconds(SEFS),coding violations(CV) and unavailable seconds (UAS) for line layer of sonet lines. Once these thresholds are exceeded, minor or major alarm is raised. Please refer RFC1595 for descriptions of ES,SES,CV,UAS

cwsLineStatisticalAlarmSeverity.name: cwsLineStatisticalAlarmSeverity
cwsLineStatisticalAlarmSeverity.description: By setting this object to major or minor, a minor or major severity alarm is raised when any statistical threshold is exceeded. By default TCA crossing does not raise any alarm.

cwsLineCurrentESsThreshold.name: cwsLineCurrentESsThreshold
cwsLineCurrentESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES) for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineTotalESsThreshold.name: cwsLineTotalESsThreshold
cwsLineTotalESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES) for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineCurrentSESsThreshold.name: cwsLineCurrentSESsThreshold
cwsLineCurrentSESsThreshold.description: This is the severely errored seconds(SES) threshold for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineTotalSESsThreshold.name: cwsLineTotalSESsThreshold
cwsLineTotalSESsThreshold.description: This is the severely errored seconds(SES) threshold for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineCurrentCVsThreshold.name: cwsLineCurrentCVsThreshold
cwsLineCurrentCVsThreshold.description: This is the Coding violations(CV) threshold for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineTotalCVsThreshold.name: cwsLineTotalCVsThreshold
cwsLineTotalCVsThreshold.description: This is the Coding violations(CV) threshold for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineCurrentUASsThreshold.name: cwsLineCurrentUASsThreshold
cwsLineCurrentUASsThreshold.description: This is the Unavailable Seconds(UAS) threshold for the current 15-min, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineTotalUASsThreshold.name: cwsLineTotalUASsThreshold
cwsLineTotalUASsThreshold.description: This is the Unavailable Seconds(UAS) threshold for the 24 hour interval above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsLineStatAlarmStatus.name: cwsLineStatAlarmStatus
cwsLineStatAlarmStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the sonet line. This object is updated every 15-minutes. Once the current 15-min window has passed, and there are no errors in the current 15-min window, the object is cleared from the lower level sonet task. The cwsLineStatAlarmStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. If none of the bits are set, it indicates no defect. The various bit-positions are: 1 sonetLineTotalESs 2 sonetLineTotalSESs 3 sonetLineTotalCVs 4 sonetLineTotalUASs 5 sonetLineCurrentESs 6 sonetLineCurrentSESs 7 sonetLineCurrentCVs 8 sonetLineCurrentUASs 9 sonetFarEndLineTotalESs 10 sonetFarEndLineTotalSESs 11 sonetFarEndLineTotalCVs 12 sonetFarEndLineTotalUASs 13 sonetFarEndLineCurrentESs 14 sonetFarEndLineCurrentSESs 15 sonetFarEndLineCurrentCVs 16 sonetFarEndLineCurrentUASs

cwsPathAlarmTable.name: cwsPathAlarmTable
cwsPathAlarmTable.description: The SONET/SDH Path Alarm table. This table contains objects for thresholds which a user can set. When any threshold is exceeded, an alarm is set. Changing any threshold will affect both the Near End and Far End(remote end of the line) threshold.

cwsPathAlarmEntry.name: cwsPathAlarmEntry
cwsPathAlarmEntry.description: An entry in the SONET/SDH Path Alarm table. Thresholds maybe specified for errored seconds(ES), severely errored seconds(SES), severely errored framing seconds(SEFS),coding violations(CV) and unavailable seconds (UAS) for path layer of sonet lines. Once these thresholds are exceeded, minor or major alarm is raised. Please refer RFC1595 for descriptions of ES,SES,SEFS,CV,UAS.

cwsPathStatisticalAlarmSeverity.name: cwsPathStatisticalAlarmSeverity
cwsPathStatisticalAlarmSeverity.description: By setting this object to major or minor, a minor or major severity alarm is raised when any statistical threshold is exceeded. By default TCA crossing does not raise any alarm.

cwsPathCurrentESsThreshold.name: cwsPathCurrentESsThreshold
cwsPathCurrentESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES) for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End (remote end of the line) and Near End(this end of the line).

cwsPathTotalESsThreshold.name: cwsPathTotalESsThreshold
cwsPathTotalESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for errored seconds(ES) for the 24-hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End (remote end of the line) and Near End(this end of the line).

cwsPathCurrentSESsThreshold.name: cwsPathCurrentSESsThreshold
cwsPathCurrentSESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored seconds(SES) for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathTotalSESsThreshold.name: cwsPathTotalSESsThreshold
cwsPathTotalSESsThreshold.description: This object indicates the threshold for severely errored seconds(SES) for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathCurrentCVsThreshold.name: cwsPathCurrentCVsThreshold
cwsPathCurrentCVsThreshold.description: This is the coding violations threshold for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathTotalCVsThreshold.name: cwsPathTotalCVsThreshold
cwsPathTotalCVsThreshold.description: This is the coding violations threshold for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathCurrentUASsThreshold.name: cwsPathCurrentUASsThreshold
cwsPathCurrentUASsThreshold.description: This is the unavailable seconds threshold for the current 15-min interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathTotalUASsThreshold.name: cwsPathTotalUASsThreshold
cwsPathTotalUASsThreshold.description: This is the unavailable seconds threshold for the 24 hour interval, above which alarm is generated. This threshold is the same for Far End and Near End.

cwsPathStatAlarmStatus.name: cwsPathStatAlarmStatus
cwsPathStatAlarmStatus.description: This variable indicates the status of the interface. The cwsPathStatAlarmStatus is a bit map represented as a sum, therefore, it can represent multiple defects simultaneously. If none of the bits are set, it indicates no defect. The following ar the bit positions: 1 sonetPathTotalESs 2 sonetPathTotalSESs 3 sonetPathTotalCVs 4 sonetPathTotalUASs 5 sonetPathCurrentESs 6 sonetPathCurrentSESs 7 sonetPathCurrentCVs 8 sonetPathCurrentUASs 9 sonetFarEndPathTotalESs 10 sonetFarEndPathTotalSESs 11 sonetFarEndPathTotalCVs 12 sonetFarEndPathTotalUASs 13 sonetFarEndPathCurrentESs 14 sonetFarEndPathCurrentSESs 15 sonetFarEndPathCurrentCVs 16 sonetFarEndPathCurrentUASs
